 men’s perceptions of women’s leadership abilities.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Other mechanisms, including peer effects (which are linked to recognition
 and conformity) and gender homophily may also be at play in the case of
 role models of the same sex.
 Gender homophily is defined as the preference for interaction with individuals
 of the same sex, and is linked to having more trust in individuals of the
 same social group 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "doi:10.1146/annurev.soc.27.1.415"

\end_inset

.
 Such mechanisms imply that the information contained in a message brought
